01:37.793 --> 01:40.970
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:41.101 --> 01:43.799
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

01:43.929 --> 01:46.802
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE.

02:02.861 --> 02:04.385
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING]

02:05.516 --> 02:07.431
-FEMALE PHOTOGRAPHER:
OKAY, GIRLS, THAT'S IT.

02:08.301 --> 02:09.693
BIG SMILE. [CAMERA CLICKING]

02:16.527 --> 02:17.920
NICE.

02:20.923 --> 02:22.185
[LAUGHING]

02:25.101 --> 02:29.975
[SLOW ROCK MUSIC]

02:35.720 --> 02:37.200
PERFECT.
[CAMERA CLICKING]

02:38.375 --> 02:39.811
BIG, BIG SMILE HERE.

03:02.225 --> 03:05.533
[PENSIVE MUSIC]

03:19.721 --> 03:21.201
-HEY, NEELY.

03:22.506 --> 03:23.899
-PETER.

03:24.029 --> 03:25.640
-GUESS YOU DIDN'T
EXPECT TO SEE ME, HUH?

03:26.467 --> 03:28.120
-YOU COULD SAY I'M
A LITTLE SURPRISED.

03:29.078 --> 03:30.166
-WELL, YOU LOOK GREAT.

03:31.950 --> 03:33.822
-THANKS. SO DO YOU.

03:35.998 --> 03:37.304
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

03:37.434 --> 03:40.350
-WELL, YOU KNOW,
TODAY WOULD'VE BEEN

03:40.481 --> 03:42.178
OUR FIFTH
WEDDING ANNIVERSARY.

03:42.309 --> 03:43.875
I, UH...

03:44.485 --> 03:46.704
I JUST WANTED TO SEE YA,
SEE HOW YOU'RE DOIN'.

03:52.667 --> 03:54.321
MAYBE I SHOULDN'T OF COME.

03:54.930 --> 03:56.410
-YOU KNOW, YOU
JUST CAN'T EXPECT ME

03:56.540 --> 03:57.846
TO WELCOME YOU BACK
WITH OPEN ARMS.

03:58.499 --> 04:00.196
-I'M SORRY, NEELY.

04:00.327 --> 04:02.198
I KNOW
I'VE MADE SOME MISTAKES,

04:02.329 --> 04:04.679
AND I'VE PAID
A GREAT PRICE FOR IT.

04:05.636 --> 04:07.203
-SO DID I.

04:08.552 --> 04:11.207
-DID I HAPPEN TO MENTION
HOW GREAT YOU LOOK?

04:14.079 --> 04:15.951
WOULD YOU HAVE DINNER
WITH ME TONIGHT?

04:16.081 --> 04:17.300
PLEASE.

04:20.564 --> 04:23.306
-OKAY.
I'LL HAVE DINNER WITH YOU.

04:40.367 --> 04:42.282
[LAUGHING, INDISTINCT
CONVERSATION]

04:48.026 --> 04:50.159
-DEREK: I GOT IT,
I GOT IT. COME ON, GUYS.

04:52.509 --> 04:54.294
-TIMMY: RIGHT OVER
HERE. THROW IT HERE!

04:56.208 --> 04:58.776
-DEREK: COME ON,
LET'S GO GET IT.

05:02.476 --> 05:03.912
-TIMMY: THERE IT IS!

05:04.042 --> 05:05.914
-I CAN SEE IT NOW.

05:08.133 --> 05:10.788
[BOYS YELLING]

05:10.919 --> 05:13.051
-DEREK: SOMEBODY HELP ME!

05:13.182 --> 05:14.836
I CAN'T STAND UP ANYMORE!

05:16.446 --> 05:19.275
SOMEBODY HELP ME! PLEASE!

05:20.537 --> 05:22.365
[BOYS YELLING IN DISTRESS]

05:24.454 --> 05:25.760
SOMEBODY HELP ME!

05:25.890 --> 05:31.331
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

05:31.461 --> 05:35.422
SOMEBODY HELP ME!
I CAN'T SWIM!

05:41.689 --> 05:43.865
[BOYS YELLING IN DISTRESS]

05:44.822 --> 05:46.346
[CHOKING, GURGLING]

05:48.565 --> 05:50.088
-TIMMY: HELP!

05:51.568 --> 05:53.004
[CHOKING, GURGLING]

05:53.657 --> 05:54.876
-WHAT'S GOIN' ON?

05:55.006 --> 05:56.443
-A RESCUE!
[CAMERA CLICKING]

06:00.795 --> 06:02.144
-HELP ME!

06:03.580 --> 06:05.147
[COUGHING, GURGLING]

06:06.496 --> 06:08.106
-MAN: OVER THERE!

06:08.237 --> 06:09.238
[CAMERA CLICKING]

06:11.283 --> 06:13.198
[BOYS YELLING INDISTINCTLY]

06:15.592 --> 06:18.639
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

06:24.471 --> 06:26.908
[BOYS HOLLERING IN DISTRESS]

06:35.090 --> 06:36.744
-BOY: HELP US!

06:41.096 --> 06:43.620
-GRAB ON. GRAB ON!

06:43.751 --> 06:45.317
ARE YOU ALRIGHT?

06:50.148 --> 06:51.062
OKAY.

07:00.158 --> 07:03.031
OKAY. GRAB ON. GRAB ON.

07:03.161 --> 07:04.598
YOU GONNA BE OKAY?
-JUAN: SI.

07:04.728 --> 07:06.295
-OKAY. GOOD.

07:06.426 --> 07:07.296
YOU GUYS OKAY?

07:10.212 --> 07:11.387
TAKE 'EM AROUND THE JETTY.

07:11.518 --> 07:13.476
I'M GOING BACK
FOR THE OTHER BOY.

07:13.607 --> 07:14.651
-OKAY.

07:15.652 --> 07:19.395
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

07:22.442 --> 07:24.792
[CAMERA CLICKING]
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

07:38.283 --> 07:39.546
-HOLD ON.

07:44.420 --> 07:46.117
-I GOT 'EM.
-OKAY. GET READY.

07:46.248 --> 07:48.685
-I GOT 'EM, TAKE THE CAN.
-GRAB ON.

07:48.816 --> 07:50.992
-ALRIGHT, LET'S TAKE 'EM
AROUND THE JETTY TO THE BEACH.

07:51.122 --> 07:52.123
COME ON.

07:52.994 --> 07:55.953
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

08:04.962 --> 08:06.311
-YOU'RE GONNA BE ALRIGHT.

08:06.442 --> 08:07.704
I'VE GOTCHA.

08:08.923 --> 08:10.490
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

08:23.590 --> 08:25.635
-MAN 1: ALRIGHT,
THEY GOT 'EM! YEAH!

08:27.376 --> 08:28.986
-MANNY, STAY WITH THEM, OKAY?

08:29.117 --> 08:30.597
-MAN 2: WAIT A MINUTE, MAN.
THERE WAS THREE OF THEM.

08:31.728 --> 08:34.121
[CROWD CHATTERING]

08:35.602 --> 08:36.951
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

08:48.310 --> 08:51.226
[INTENSE MUSIC]

09:37.838 --> 09:42.843
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

09:56.204 --> 09:57.509
[COUGHING]

10:02.645 --> 10:04.299
-HE'S BREATHING.

10:07.998 --> 10:09.826
-OKAY.
LET ME HELP.

10:09.957 --> 10:12.786
-LET'S SWIM IN.
-OKAY.

10:13.482 --> 10:15.005
[SIREN BLARING]

10:20.794 --> 10:22.622
-I GOT HIS LEGS!

10:23.840 --> 10:28.279
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]
[SIREN BLARING]

10:38.942 --> 10:40.030
-CAROLINE:
OKAY, SET HIM DOWN.

10:40.161 --> 10:41.379
WATCH HIS HEAD.

10:46.602 --> 10:48.125
HE STOPPED BREATHING AGAIN.

10:59.484 --> 11:00.834
-NEELY: HE'S GOT A PULSE.

11:06.666 --> 11:08.232
-HE'S BREATHING.

11:09.190 --> 11:11.018
HIS PUPILS ARE DILATED.

11:17.938 --> 11:22.072
[SPEAKING SPANISH]

11:24.074 --> 11:26.773
HEY, CAN YOU HEAR ME?
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

11:28.035 --> 11:29.689
WHAT'S HIS NAME?
DOES ANYBODY KNOW HIS NAME?

11:29.819 --> 11:31.255
-CUAL ES EL NOMBRE DE TU AMIGO?
-DEREK.

11:31.386 --> 11:33.954
-DEREK. HIS NAME'S DEREK.
-DEREK. HI, DEREK.

11:34.084 --> 11:36.739
HEY, CAN YOU HEAR ME?
HUH? CAN YOU HEAR ME?

11:36.870 --> 11:38.610
IF YOU CAN HEAR ME,
MOVE YOUR FINGERS.

11:38.741 --> 11:40.308
COME ON, DEREK.
MOVE YOUR FINGERS.

11:43.659 --> 11:45.052
-I'VE GOT CAPILLARY REFILL.

11:45.182 --> 11:46.618
-DEREK, COME ON.

11:46.749 --> 11:48.316
MOVE YOUR FINGERS
FOR ME. PLEASE?

11:48.446 --> 11:50.405
PLEASE? COME ON, YOU CAN DO IT.
MOVE YOUR FINGERS.

11:50.535 --> 11:52.799
-ALL RIGHT. WE'RE
READY TO ROLL ON THREE.

11:52.929 --> 11:54.931
ONE, TWO, THREE.

11:55.062 --> 11:56.324
THERE WE GO.

11:56.454 --> 11:57.847
BACK.

12:01.459 --> 12:02.678
-CAROLINE: I GOT THIS.

12:05.420 --> 12:06.421
-WE'RE GONNA LIFT ON THREE.

12:06.551 --> 12:09.859
READY? ONE, TWO, THREE.

12:11.948 --> 12:13.733
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

12:20.609 --> 12:22.393
[SIREN BLARING]

12:26.963 --> 12:28.878
-DO YOU SPEAK ENGLISH?
-NO.

12:29.487 --> 12:31.620
-HE UNDERSTANDS IT.
HE'S JUST AFRAID TO SPEAK IT.

12:31.751 --> 12:33.535
WHAT ABOUT DEREK?
IS HE DEAD?

12:33.665 --> 12:35.189
-NO. NO, HONEY,
HE'S NOT DEAD.

12:35.319 --> 12:37.017
HE, HE JUST WENT
TO THE HOSPITAL.

12:37.147 --> 12:39.236
LISTEN, I'M GONNA NEED
HIS PARENT'S NUMBER, OKAY?

12:39.367 --> 12:41.195
-HE DOESN'T HAVE
ANY PARENTS.

12:42.022 --> 12:42.849
WE LIVE IN A SHELTER.

12:42.979 --> 12:44.111
WE'RE HOMELESS KIDS.

12:44.241 --> 12:46.504
WE CAME TO THE BEACH ON A BUS.

12:46.635 --> 12:48.332
MRS. JOHNSON DOESN'T
KNOW WE'RE HERE.

12:48.463 --> 12:49.943
SHE'S GONNA BE MAD.

12:50.073 --> 12:51.683
-LOOK, I'M GONNA HAVE
TO CALL HER, ALRIGHT?

12:52.510 --> 12:53.990
COME ON, GUYS. LET'S GO.

12:54.121 --> 12:55.862
OH, UH...

12:55.992 --> 12:58.081
WHAT ABOUT YOUR FRIEND?
WHERE'S YOUR FRIEND?

12:59.866 --> 13:01.128
YOU KNOW, THE BOY.

13:01.258 --> 13:02.651
UH, HE WAS STANDING
ON THE ROCKS.

13:02.782 --> 13:04.131
THE BOY WHO POINTED OUT
TO WHERE DEREK WAS.

13:04.261 --> 13:06.002
-NO OTHER FRIEND CAME WITH US.

13:06.133 --> 13:07.830
IT WAS JUST THE THREE OF US.

13:11.616 --> 13:13.314
-OKAY. COME ON.

13:18.014 --> 13:21.409
[MONITOR BEEPING]
[SLOW MUSIC]

13:45.433 --> 13:47.609
-I HOPE HE'S GONNA BE OKAY.

13:47.739 --> 13:49.263
-YOU DID EVERYTHING YOU COULD.

13:49.393 --> 13:51.831
IT'S AMAZING YOU FOUND HIM
AS QUICKLY AS YOU DID.

13:51.961 --> 13:53.484
-WELL, I NEVER WOULD'VE
FOUND HIM IF THAT BOY

13:53.615 --> 13:55.704
ON THE ROCKS HADN'T
POINTED OUT WHERE HE WAS.

13:55.835 --> 13:57.924
[APPROACHING FOOTSTEPS]

14:01.101 --> 14:02.450
HOW IS HE?

14:02.580 --> 14:04.452
-WELL, HE STILL HASN'T
REGAINED CONSCIOUSNESS.

14:04.582 --> 14:06.019
BUT HIS BREATHING IS STRONG,

14:06.149 --> 14:07.585
SO WE'RE JUST GONNA
HAVE TO WAIT AND SEE.

14:07.716 --> 14:08.891
[BEEPING]

14:09.022 --> 14:09.979
-LET US KNOW IF
ANYTHING CHANGES?

14:10.110 --> 14:12.025
-YES, CERTAINLY. EXCUSE ME.

14:18.118 --> 14:19.859
-THESE ARE THE LIFEGUARDS
THAT HELPED US, MISS JOHNSON.

14:19.989 --> 14:21.948
-HI. I'M, I'M CAROLINE HOLDEN.

14:22.078 --> 14:23.427
THIS IS NEELY AND MANNY.

14:23.558 --> 14:24.428
-HI.
-NEELY: HI.

14:24.559 --> 14:26.517
-HI. I'M TAYLOR JOHNSON.

14:26.648 --> 14:28.868
JUAN AND TIMMY TOLD ME
WHAT HAPPENED.

14:28.998 --> 14:31.305
THANK YOU FOR EVERYTHING
THAT YOU'VE DONE.

14:32.045 --> 14:32.915
HOW IS DEREK?

14:34.047 --> 14:37.659
-UM, HE HAS NOT REGAINED
CONSCIOUSNESS YET.

14:37.789 --> 14:42.925
-[SIGHS] THE BOYS HAVE NEVER
BEEN TO THE BEACH BEFORE,

14:43.056 --> 14:45.580
AND NONE OF THEM REALLY
KNOW HOW TO SWIM.

14:48.931 --> 14:50.890
OH, GOD. [CRYING]

14:53.631 --> 14:54.545
DEREK.

14:56.373 --> 14:58.723
[SLOW MUSIC]

15:15.392 --> 15:17.177
-WHOA!

15:17.307 --> 15:19.266
YOU'RE A LITTLE OVERDRESSED
FOR DEBRIEFING, AREN'T YOU?

15:19.396 --> 15:20.876
-WELL, I'VE GOT A DATE TONIGHT.

15:21.007 --> 15:22.660
-OH, REALLY?
-YEAH.

15:22.791 --> 15:24.358
-OH. IT WOULDN'T HAPPEN TO
BE WITH THAT GORGEOUS HUNK

15:24.488 --> 15:26.447
OF A MAN I SAW YOU WITH
THIS MORNING, WOULD IT? HUH?

15:26.577 --> 15:27.578
WHO IS HE?

15:27.709 --> 15:29.711
-ACTUALLY, HE'S A...

15:29.841 --> 15:30.930
HE'S MY EX-HUSBAND.

15:32.453 --> 15:33.976
-REALLY? [LAUGHS]

15:34.107 --> 15:36.022
6WOW. I, I HAD NO IDEA YOU
WERE EVER EVEN MARRIED.

15:36.674 --> 15:38.633
-WELL, PETER WAS MY FIRST LOVE.

15:39.286 --> 15:41.288
WE GOT MARRIED RIGHT
OUTTA HIGH SCHOOL.

15:42.158 --> 15:44.378
WE'VE BEEN DIVORCED
TWO YEARS.

15:44.508 --> 15:45.814
-WHAT HAPPENED?

15:45.945 --> 15:47.685
-I DON'T KNOW.
LONELINESS, I GUESS.

15:47.816 --> 15:49.339
HE WORKED ALL THE TIME.

15:49.470 --> 15:51.167
HE'S A COMMERCIAL DIVER,
SO HE TRAVELED A LOT.

15:51.298 --> 15:54.866
AND MY LIFE REVOLVED AROUND HIS.

15:54.997 --> 15:58.000
HE COULD NEVER UNDERSTAND
WHY I WASN'T HAPPY.

15:58.131 --> 15:59.915
-AND YOU'RE JUST, YOU'RE GONNA
GO OUT WITH THIS MAN AGAIN?

16:00.046 --> 16:01.612
-I DON'T KNOW.

16:01.743 --> 16:03.614
HE SAID THAT HE WAS SORRY,
THAT HE MADE MISTAKES.

16:09.490 --> 16:10.708
-JUST YOU BE CAREFUL, ALRIGHT?

16:10.839 --> 16:12.493
DON'T MAKE ANY
MISTAKES YOURSELF.

16:12.623 --> 16:14.190
-I WON'T. THANKS.

16:18.368 --> 16:21.371
-OKAY. WE ALL KNOW WHY WE'RE
HERE, SO LET'S GET STARTED.

16:21.502 --> 16:24.766
I WANTED TO HOLD THIS DEBRIEFING
WHERE THE RESCUE TOOK PLACE

16:24.896 --> 16:27.116
TO MAKE SURE WE FOLLOWED
PROPER PROCEDURE.

16:27.247 --> 16:28.639
-IS THERE ANY
UPDATE ON THE BOY?

16:28.770 --> 16:31.294
-CAROLINE, THE BOY
IS STILL UNCONSCIOUS.

16:31.425 --> 16:32.904
BUT HE'S BREATHING.

16:33.035 --> 16:34.515
THEY DON'T KNOW YET IF
THERE'S ANY BRAIN DAMAGE.

16:34.645 --> 16:36.604
NOW, THERE IS A
SLIGHT DISCREPANCY

16:36.734 --> 16:38.519
BETWEEN THE INCIDENT REPORTS.

16:38.649 --> 16:40.390
CAROLINE.

16:40.521 --> 16:43.002
YOUR REPORT STATES THERE WAS
A FOURTH BOY ON THE ROCKS.

16:43.132 --> 16:44.960
NEELY'S REPORT
DOESN'T MENTION HIM.

16:45.091 --> 16:47.702
-THAT WAS THE BOY WHO POINTED
TO WHERE DEREK WAS SUBMERGED.

16:47.832 --> 16:50.226
-SO NEELY, SINCE THE
BOY WASN'T A VICTIM,

16:50.357 --> 16:52.576
YOU JUST OMITTED HIM
FROM YOUR REPORT?

16:52.707 --> 16:54.709
-I NEVER SAY ANOTHER BOY
ON THE ROCKS.

16:57.233 --> 16:58.582
-I DIDN'T SEE ANYBODY EITHER.

16:59.670 --> 17:01.803
-HE WAS THERE.
-CHRIS?

17:01.933 --> 17:03.109
-I DIDN'T SEE
ANYONE OUT THERE.

17:05.328 --> 17:07.069
-GUYS, I'M, I'M NOT CRAZY.

17:07.200 --> 17:09.289
-LOOK. KIDS CAN MOVE
REAL FAST.

17:09.419 --> 17:11.464
I'M SURE THERE'S A LOGICAL
EXPLANATION FOR THIS.

17:11.595 --> 17:14.598
-YEAH.
THERE WAS A BOY ON THE ROCKS.

17:17.513 --> 17:18.602
HE WAS THERE.

17:19.429 --> 17:21.257
[MONITOR BEEPING]

17:21.387 --> 17:23.781
-I KNOW YOU'RE GONNA
PULL THROUGH THIS, DEREK.

17:24.608 --> 17:28.002
YOUR FRIENDS ARE KINDA WORRIED
ABOUT YOU, BUT...

17:28.569 --> 17:30.875
I'D REALLY LIKE TO GET A
CHANCE TO KNOW YOU AND...

17:31.528 --> 17:33.617
MAYBE WE COULD BE FRIENDS.

17:33.748 --> 17:36.142
I COULD TAKE YOU FOR
AN ICE CREAM, OR...

17:36.881 --> 17:38.144
MAYBE YOU COULD COME
DOWN TO THE BEACH

17:38.274 --> 17:39.710
AND I COULD TEACH YOU TO SWIM.

17:39.841 --> 17:41.190
-MALE DOCTOR: HI.

17:41.321 --> 17:42.713
-HI.

17:42.844 --> 17:43.975
-WOULD YOU EXCUSE ME
WHILE I CHECK ON DEREK?

17:44.106 --> 17:46.021
-OH, YEAH, OF COURSE.
-THANKS.

17:47.153 --> 17:48.937
[RECEDING FOOTSTEPS]

17:49.938 --> 17:53.550
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

18:08.478 --> 18:10.176
STILL NO CHANGE
IN HIS CONDITION.

18:11.873 --> 18:14.310
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

18:23.711 --> 18:25.408
-DOCTOR, WHO'S THAT
BOY STANDING THERE?

18:25.539 --> 18:26.409
-WHAT BOY?

18:26.540 --> 18:27.671
-THAT...

18:29.499 --> 18:31.022
WELL, HE WAS...

18:31.153 --> 18:32.763
HE WAS JUST THERE.

18:32.894 --> 18:34.635
HE LOOKED EXACTLY LIKE THE BOY
WHO I SAW ON THE ROCKS.

18:34.765 --> 18:36.550
-WHAT BOY ON THE ROCKS?

18:43.383 --> 18:45.646
-THAT'S THE STRANGEST THING.

18:48.344 --> 18:50.520
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]
[MONITOR BEEPING]

18:56.352 --> 18:57.527
[FAST BEEPING]

19:01.314 --> 19:03.707
-BREATHING AND PULSE
ARE NORMALIZING.

19:03.838 --> 19:05.056
EVERYTHING LOOKS STABLE.

19:07.798 --> 19:09.539
DEREK, CAN YOU HEAR ME?

19:12.412 --> 19:14.196
-OH, MY GOD.

19:15.415 --> 19:16.633
DOCTOR, LOOK.

19:18.679 --> 19:20.898
[HOPEFUL MUSIC]

19:44.444 --> 19:46.794
-HI.
-HI. HOW'S DEREK?

19:46.924 --> 19:48.926
-OH... WELL,
HE REGAINED CONSCIOUSNESS,

19:49.057 --> 19:50.276
BUT THE DOCTOR WANTS
TO KEEP HIM THERE

19:50.406 --> 19:52.016
TO RUN A FEW TESTS.
-OH.

19:52.147 --> 19:53.670
-OH! HOW WAS YOUR DATE?

19:53.801 --> 19:55.455
-OH. CONFUSING.

19:55.585 --> 19:56.934
I DON'T KNOW.

19:57.065 --> 19:59.067
-HM. WOULD YOU LIKE
TO TALK ABOUT IT?

19:59.198 --> 20:01.809
-DATING YOUR EX-HUSBAND
IS SO STRANGE.

20:01.939 --> 20:03.898
ALL I KEPT THINKING ABOUT WAS

20:04.028 --> 20:05.639
THE MEMORIES AND THE PAST.

20:05.769 --> 20:08.468
I DON'T KNOW IF THEY'RE
REAL OR IF I'M JUST...

20:09.033 --> 20:10.470
RELIVING MY MEMORIES.

20:10.600 --> 20:12.298
-OKAY. THINK ABOUT THIS.

20:12.428 --> 20:13.212
MAYBE...

20:13.342 --> 20:14.996
PETER'S YOUR TRUE LOVE.

20:15.126 --> 20:16.737
AND YOU'RE HAVING
ALL THESE FEELINGS

20:16.867 --> 20:18.347
BECAUSE HE'S THE ONE YOU'RE
REALLY MEANT TO BE WITH.

